  "text": "For this study, we used one human lung adenocarcinoma cell line PC14PE6/AS2 (AS2) to study the effect of IL-6 downstream pathways on IL-6 autocrine production and drug resistance. We had previously established this cell line and found it to produce autocrine IL-6 which activated Stat3 and subsequently promoted tumor progression [CITATION_1] . In addition, we used a series of AS2-derived cell lines: one vector cell line (AS2/Vec-11) and 6 mutant cell lines expressing plasmids containing constitutively-active (AS2/S3C cells: AS2/S3C-A and AS2/S3C-C) or dominant-negative Stat3 (AS2/S3D cells: AS2/S3D-8, AS2/S3D-9, and AS2/ S3F cells: AS2/S3F-3, and AS2/S3F-7).",
